V:8 name="Bass I"     clef=bass
%
% ══════════════════════════════════════════════
% PHRASE 1 — bars 1–4
% SSAA alone (bars 1–2); TTBB enters at bar 3
% ══════════════════════════════════════════════
%
% V1 (S1): follows soprano exactly
% V2 (S2): diatonic third below S1; opens with S1+S2 unison D4 for blend
% V3 (A1): follows original alto (S1V2)
% V4 (A2): diatonic third below A1
% V5 (T1): silent bars 1–2; enters bar 3 with original tenor line
% V6 (T2): silent bars 1–2; enters bar 3 a diatonic third below T1
% V7 (Bar): silent bars 1–2; enters bar 3 a diatonic third above bass
% V8 (B1): silent bars 1–2; enters bar 3 with original bass line
%
[V:1] [Q:1/4=100] D2 F A | A3/2 G/ F2 | E2 E G | G3/2 F/ E2 |
